I have orb weavers build webs on my back porch each summer, usually under my porch light, so I’ve done some reading on them. They are interesting spiders, and this is coming from someone with arachnophobia. The webs are huge. The male will stand on the edge of the web and pluck the strands to sort of ring the doorbell, announcing his presence, so he doesn’t get eaten on the way to the female. I’ve seen them do this, which was interesting to watch. Then I knocked him off the side of the web and into the grass (still alive) because I was not giving my blessing to a bunch of baby spiders. They can only so interesting before that arachnophobia kicks back in again.
